Meet <b>Bella</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Bella moved to Metro Park in November 2005 and lives at <a href='/home/?user=nlightened'>69529 Timberwolf Way</a>. She likes to split her time between acting, drawing, and solving mysteries. <br><br>With that Millsberry Match Wanted trophy on display, solving mysteries may be more than just a hobby for Bella. She has also taken a noticeable interest in the deep expanses of outerspace by mastering both Galactic Defender and Countdown. Bella's currently sporting her Cleopatra costume for Halloween, but it seems like she may be putting on an Astronaut suit in the near future. I'm sure the transition to freeze-dried ice cream will be a smooth one.  <br><br>Bella has quite the taste in music, listening to the Big Band, Country, and Classic Rock genres. <br><br>Mixing the music up is probably helpful when you're trying to get the creative juices flowing for a little painting. If Bella invites you over to cross brushes in her fabulous Atrium, just be sure not to get any paint on her designer rug. Her favorite color is violet; so try not to hog it all.<br><br>If it's a nice day you may want to take a dip in her wonderful oasis of a swimming pool for a little water volleyball.  I would personally head towards the shallow end, though. It's hard to return serves while treading water. <br><br>The next time you bump into Bella, be sure to thank her and congratulate her on being such an outstanding citizen. <br></div>
